Matron Eyl's Trunk is a storied archive-container associated with custody of sensitive instructional fragments at Wizard's Keep.
It takes its name from Matron Eyl, a senior administrator at Wizard's Keep during the late institutional period when the Keep's internal governance was contested.
The Trunk is not a single object but a designation: the collection of documents, instruction fragments, and sealed correspondence Eyl personally catalogued and secured.
Her method was distinctive: she separated instructional fragments by their risk classification rather than their subject matter, organizing by consequence of misuse rather than by content.
This meant related materials were physically separated across the Trunk's subdivisions, making piecemeal theft harder but also making legitimate research more laborious.
The Trunk survived two succession disputes within Wizard's Keep because Eyl's organizational method meant no faction could easily locate the materials they wanted.
After Eyl's death, the Trunk's custody passed to a succession of administrators who could use the collection but could not fully reorganize it without losing the protective structure.
The Trunk is currently understood to contain: sealed warrant fragments from Midgaard's Violet Compact, early Kelshadra instructional drafts, and at least one sealed correspondence chain from Kel'Shadra.
Access is restricted to senior Keep administrators and requires cross-attestation under Wizard's Keep governance protocols.
Midgaard, Kiess, and Kowloon have each requested access to specific sections at least once; all three were denied or deferred under Keep custody protocols.
The Trunk is considered one of the most significant surviving collections of contested-provenance institutional documents in the five-city corridor.

