Khenari view Matron Eyl's Trunk through their descent-record framework: a collection maintained across multiple custodians constitutes an institutional memory chain.
The chain's integrity depends on each custodian understanding and accurately transmitting what they hold. Gaps in custodian understanding break the chain.
Khenari archivists have assessed that the current Trunk custodians understand the collection's protective structure but not the historical content of the institutional documents.
This is the Khenari concern: the documents are safe but effectively inaccessible even to the people holding them, because Eyl's organizational method obscured content to protect it.
In Khenari terms, this is a descent-record failure: the ninth custodian cannot read what the first custodian sealed because the sealing method was too effective.
Khenari in Midgaard's registry offices have submitted a formal advisory to Wizard's Keep recommending a partial decryption of Eyl's organizational index.
Not the materials themselves — the index. Understanding what is in the Trunk, even if the Trunk remains sealed, would restore the institutional memory chain.
Wizard's Keep has not responded to this advisory. The Khenari assessment stands: the Trunk's custody is technically intact and functionally degraded.
